article.headline: Winthrop 60, Weber State 49
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- Torrell Martin scored 13 points and James Shuler added 12 to lead Winthrop to a 60-49 win over Weber State on Saturday. The Eagles (3-2) led by 29-26 at the half after a sluggish start. Winthrop was up 14-12 with 8:46 remaining in the first half and then went on an 11-0 run. With 13:37 left in the second half, Winthrop was up by 11 and would see the lead grow to as much as 17 with 1:37 left in the game. David Patton's jumper and Dale Parson's 3-pointer helped Weber State (2-1) trim the lead to 6 points, but that's as close as the Wildcats would get. Lance Allred had nine of his 10 points in the first half and lead Weber State's scoring. Brett Cox and Terrell Stovall both added eight points.
